WSL stands for Windows Subsystem for Linux. 
    It is a Windows feature that allows users to run a GNU/Linux environmen

WSL commands:        open powershell in ADMIN mode

version check:
      wsl --list -v    
      wsl –version
      wsl –status

Installation:
  WSL:
          wsl --install
          this will install ubuntu in windows
          it will take you to default linux mount created in windows as below
                    aab@LAPTOP-BQG3KNAN:/mnt/c$
                to come out of mount type:
                    aab@LAPTOP-BQG3KNAN:/mnt/c$ exit    <--
    
      check installed components in WSL:
          PS C:\> wsl --list -v
    
                NAME      STATE           VERSION
              * Ubuntu    Stopped         2
    
      to start ubuntu in WSL:
            PS C:\> wsl -d ubuntu
  zstd:   on WSL
         sudo apt-get install zstd

  ollama:  on WSL
        curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh

  @larksuiteoapi/node-sdk:   on WSL
        npm install @larksuiteoapi/node-sdk
    
  openclaw:  on WSL
        curl -fsSL https://openclaw.ai/install.sh | bash        

